
This pass is to build before and after instruction set for each instruction.
It can serve as an pre-pass for inter-procedural analysis. 

Instruction is 
1. the first instruction of a basic block, before set contains last instructions of all its pred
2. the last instruction of a basic block, after set contains first instructions of all its succ
3. a call site, after set contains the first instruction of the called function
4. a return, after set contains all following instructions of its call site. 


